27/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis said Wednesday (26 May) that boosting the competitiveness of local industry is the chief priority of the government's economic programme.
Karamanlis identified continuously declining competitiveness as a major problem, along with high inflation and unemployment.
The government plans to pursue a policy of fiscal revitalisation and economic growth aimed at creating more jobs.
(ANA, MPA - 26/05/04)
